### ### ### #### ### ### ### First try to start a focused terminal ### ### ### #### ### ### ### 
# This is rather convoluted and buggy as hell, replaced with a for_window [class="Sakura"] focus.
# It uses the pythonscript from here: https://i3wm.org/docs/user-contributed/workspace-current-output.html
# to always bring the workspace containing the terminal-emulator to the active display. As the python script 
# only works with number it moves it to "9". After that a rename script is called, that contains a sleep command
# and renames it to "5:Terminal" (hardcoded for now), after its created 
#
# Left in, as it may come handy, to have a way to start a workspace always on the active display
#
# bindsym $mod+Return exec sakura; exec --no-startup-id ~/.config/scripts/switch-workspace.py 9; exec --no-startup-id ~/.config/scripts/i3workspacehack.sh
### ### ### ### ### ### ### ### ### ### #### ### ### ### ### ### ### #### ### ### ### 

